My volt meter does not measure amps(or at least if it does I don't know how
to use it as such). I think it just does Voltage (DC), Resistance, dwell,
RPMs & diode. It is a SunPro CP7676. My other meter is a Wavetek 5xl, It
only measures Voltage (DC&AC

My other meter measures voltage (AC & DC), Resistance, and I think Amperage
- but I only getting readings of zero when I test that. So I'm not sure if I
am using it correctly. It is a Wavetek 5XL.

I hooked my meter between the ground strap and the body, and consistently
get readings over 12V. I unhooked each fuse, one at a time, and the readings
stayed the same. This make me think I am leaking power somewhere before the
fuses, does that sound right? 

My vehicle had been upgraded from a generator to an alternator. 

